      "span_text": "Instead, iPSCs display an almost complete epigenetic reset, whereas iNs maintain most of the epigenetic marks, a phenomenon that is comprehensively addressed by Denoth-Lippuner and Jessberger in this issue  . iNSCs can be produced faster and more cost-efficient than iPSC-derived NSCs, and also harbor less tumor formation potential."
